<topic id="id_4" class="- topic/topic "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze the test execution flow</title><body class="- topic/body "><p class="- topic/p ">We first analyze the recorded test case to identify where we can apply control flow commands.</p><p class="- topic/p ">The recorded test case shows that the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">click</codeph> and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">verifyText</codeph> commands are repeatedly used.</p><p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/conditional-and-loop-tutorial/KR-5.8.0-test-case-recorded-repeated-steps.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Repeated commands in the test case</alt></image>
        </p><p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Target</b> fields of the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">click</codeph> and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">verifyText</codeph> commands are:</p><table class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Command</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Target</entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry "> <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">click</i>
                        </entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">
                            <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock ">xpath=//main[@id='main']/div[2]/ul/li[{index
                     value}]/div/a[2]</codeblock>
                        </entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry "> <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">verifyText</i>
                        </entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">
                            <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock ">xpath=//main[@id='main']/div[2]/ul/li[{index
                     value}]/div/a[3]</codeblock>
                        </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">From the XPath in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Target</b> field, we can see that each item has a unique index value. The associated index value is incremented because the items are selected from the top to the bottom of the page.</p><p class="- topic/p "> <image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-recorder/docs/conditional-and-loop-tutorial/KR-5.8.0-test-case-recorded-patterns.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Repeated commands in the test case</alt></image>
        </p><p class="- topic/p ">Knowing that each item is associated with one index value, we can use control flow commands to automatically iterate over, select, and verify all 12 items on the page.</p></body></topic>